{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-template-js","path":"/ideas/universe-simulator","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2 id=\"liquid-simulation\" style=\"position:relative;\">Liquid simulation<a href=\"#liquid-simulation\" aria-label=\"liquid simulation permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>Using a cubic polynomial for cohesion/repulsion seems to work great; you can customize the cubic per fluid type just by storing the abcd of \"a + b<em>x + c</em>x^2 + d*x^3\", and get behaviors like slimy, clay-like, and porous/brittle. No if statements or LUTs needed.</p>\n<p>It's particles and uses position-based dynamics, and it's simulated on the GPU :)</p>\n<p>The fluid sim is PBF (Position-Based Fluids) with some modifications. PBF uses various ideas from SPH.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 598px; flex:0.5451505016722408;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/91a35edf76cd09e23ba0d2f11db27076/0c69d/liquid-simulation.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 183.4355828220859%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"liquid simulation\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/91a35edf76cd09e23ba0d2f11db27076/0c69d/liquid-simulation.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/91a35edf76cd09e23ba0d2f11db27076/222b7/liquid-simulation.png 163w,\n/static/91a35edf76cd09e23ba0d2f11db27076/ff46a/liquid-simulation.png 325w,\n/static/91a35edf76cd09e23ba0d2f11db27076/0c69d/liquid-simulation.png 598w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 598px) 100vw, 598px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://twitter.com/MytinoGames/status/1531462046449008641\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://twitter.com/MytinoGames/status/1531462046449008641</a></p>\n<p><strong>Position based fluids</strong> <a href=\"https://mmacklin.com/pbf_sig_preprint.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://mmacklin.com/pbf_sig_preprint.pdf</a> where they use Newton steps <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newton%27s_method_in_optimization\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Newton%27s_method_in_optimization</a> and Gradients <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient</a> (not to be confused with ML term <em>Gradient descent</em> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient_descent\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gradient_descent</a>)</p>\n<h2 id=\"fractal-planet-generator\" style=\"position:relative;\">Fractal planet generator<a href=\"#fractal-planet-generator\" aria-label=\"fractal planet generator permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>This was originally written by a PHD from Denmark - John Olsson</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Code: <a href=\"http://www.lysator.liu.se/~johol/fwmg/source/worldgen.c\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://www.lysator.liu.se/~johol/fwmg/source/worldgen.c</a></li>\n<li>How it works: <a href=\"http://www.lysator.liu.se/~johol/fwmg/howisitdone.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">http://www.lysator.liu.se/~johol/fwmg/howisitdone.html</a></li>\n<li>Homepage: <a href=\"https://www.lysator.liu.se/~johol/fwmg/fwmg.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.lysator.liu.se/~johol/fwmg/fwmg.html</a></li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 650px; flex:1.6464646464646464;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/b1c31/fractal-world-map-generator.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 60.73619631901841%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"texture in godot\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/a6d36/fractal-world-map-generator.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/222b7/fractal-world-map-generator.png 163w,\n/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/ff46a/fractal-world-map-generator.png 325w,\n/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/a6d36/fractal-world-map-generator.png 650w,\n/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/e548f/fractal-world-map-generator.png 975w,\n/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/3c492/fractal-world-map-generator.png 1300w,\n/static/8337bd82f9def3a03d4b9125f1f88ccf/b1c31/fractal-world-map-generator.png 1413w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 650px) 100vw, 650px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Somewhat related (but really awesome) websites</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://dinosaurpictures.org/ancient-earth#66\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Ancient Earth Globe</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.lakepowell.net/sciencecenter/future.htm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">How The World Might Look in the Future</a> by Paleontological Science Center</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"more-fractals\" style=\"position:relative;\">More fractals<a href=\"#more-fractals\" aria-label=\"more fractals permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://fractal.institute/create-fractals/the-mandelbulb-3d-master-training-resource-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Fractal Institute</a> - many many links on that page. Very big scene on Deviant Art</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://mb3d.overwhale.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Mandelbulb3D</a>, one of many  <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XYxNFyd_EiQ\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">tutorials</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"shaders\" style=\"position:relative;\">Shaders<a href=\"#shaders\" aria-label=\"shaders permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4tVSRw\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">a planet</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"Liquid simulation Using a cubic polynomial for cohesion/repulsion seems to work great; you can customize the cubic per fluid type just by…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#liquid-simulation\">Liquid simulation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#fractal-planet-generator\">Fractal planet generator</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#more-fractals\">More fractals</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#shaders\">Shaders</a></li>\n</ul>","field